      "source": [
        "## 2. Data Cleaning and Creation of Subset Dataframes"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "collapsed": false,
        "pycharm": {
          "name": "#%% md\n"
        },
        "id": "REhTScu3JpHw",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "After reviewing the [PIAAC Household Sample Codebook](https://nces.ed.gov/pubs2016/data/2016667REV_codebook.pdf),\n",
        "most of the missing values are determined to be skipped responses (survey skip logic) or non-responses.\n",
        "For example: WRITWORK_Categorized has 2286 valid skip response, 177 not stated response, and 1145 zero responses. \n",
        "Since we are using the continuous version of WRITWORK, the total missing value is 3608.\n",
        "\n",
        "This analysis is not inferential in nature, we are looking at participants\n",
        "who responded to the survey items and have a valid scores for the cognitive assessments. Futher reading of missing data in cluser analysis can be found in Everitt, Landau, & Leese (2001)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Vx6HLbh6nUnF",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 2.1 Merge Dataframes of bkg, lit, num, and psl"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rGPX19OtYg74",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [

        "data = pd.merge(bkg, lit, on ='SEQID')\n",
        "data = pd.merge(data, num, on = 'SEQID')\n",
        "data = pd.merge(data, psl, on = 'SEQID')"
      ],

      "source": [
        "### 2.2 Visualization and Descriptive Statistics \n",
        " We plotted the charts again to view any drastic change to the variables in the dataset"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "pycharm": {
          "name": "#%%\n"
        },
        "id": "YiIm2sBKJpH0",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 0
        },
        "outputId": "9cce829c-fa0a-4a43-f26f-7dac064da6d1"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Drop Sequence ID for Plotting\n",
        "df2 = data_cleaned.drop(\"SEQID\", axis = 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Countplot of Genders\n",
        "sns.set_style(\"darkgrid\")\n",
        "sns.countplot(x = 'GENDER_R', data = df2)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Frequency Plot of Genders: Male (1.0), Female (2.0)\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "# Countplot of Education Levels\n",
        "sns.set_style(\"darkgrid\")\n",
        "sns.countplot(x = 'B_Q01A', data = df2)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Frequency Plot of Highest Education by ISCED Level\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Countplot of Employment Status\n",
        "sns.set_style(\"darkgrid\")\n",
        "sns.countplot(x = 'C_D05', data = df2)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Frequency Plot of Employment Status\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "bkg.C_D05.value_counts() # There are 5 counts in 4\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plotting Index variables\n",
        "# KDE plot of ICT skills used at home and at work\n",
        "sns.kdeplot(df2.ICTHOME, kernel=\"gau\", label = \"ICTHOME\")\n",
        "sns.kdeplot(df2.ICTWORK, kernel= \"gau\", label = \"ICTWORK\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Kernel Density Estimation Plot of ICTHOME and ICTWORK Index\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# KDE plot of Reading skills used at home and at work\n",
        "sns.kdeplot(df2.READHOME, kernel=\"gau\", label = \"READHOME\")\n",
        "sns.kdeplot(df2.READWORK, kernel= \"gau\", label = \"READWORK\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Kernel Density Estimation Plot of READHOME and READWORK Index\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# KDE plot of Writing skills used at home and at work\n",
        "sns.kdeplot(df2.WRITHOME, kernel=\"gau\", label = \"WRITHOME\")\n",
        "sns.kdeplot(df2.WRITWORK, kernel= \"gau\", label = \"WRITWORK\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Kernel Density Estimation Plot of WRITHOME and WRITWORK Index\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# KDE plot of Numeracy skills used at home and at work\n",
        "sns.kdeplot(df2.NUMHOME, kernel=\"gau\", label = \"NUMHOME\")\n",
        "sns.kdeplot(df2.NUMWORK, kernel= \"gau\", label = \"NUMWORK\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Kernel Density Estimation Plot of NUMHOME and NUMWORK Index\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Box plot of the index (pandas boxplot)\n",
        "df2.boxplot(column=['ICTHOME', \"ICTWORK\", \"READHOME\", \"READWORK\", \"NUMHOME\", \"NUMWORK\", \"WRITHOME\", \"WRITWORK\"],\n",
        "           grid = False, rot= 45, fontsize = 10)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Box-and-Whisker Plot of Index in Background Variables - Cleaned\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",

      },
      "source": [
        "## 3. Cluster Analysis"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VA5q4WQel5xG",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 3.1 K-means clustering \n",
        "\n",
        "CRISP - Data Mining Methodology"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "niQyV26iywj_",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "[Scikit-learn K-means](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/clustering.html#k-means) algorithm cluster data by iertia/within cluster sum of squares. "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "paPm-DRIyxRk",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn import metrics"
      ],
      "execution_count": 31,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VGFOIjknmowb",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "##### 3.1.1 Model 1 with Subset 1\n",
        "We assume there are 5 clusters based on how proficiceny levels are set up in PIAAC with scores range between 0-500 for each corresponding achievement levels"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YzNd0rJxmIhc",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "# Conduct kmean clustering to fit subset 1 data \n",
        "# k-means++ initialization scheme is suggested to produce more favorable results than random initialization\n",
        "five_cluster = KMeans(n_clusters=5, init = 'k-means++', n_init=30, max_iter=300, random_state= 30).fit(subset1)\n",
        "# Array for cluster assignment from the five cluster result\n",
        "five_cluster_labels = five_cluster.labels_\n",
        "# Centroids of the 5 cluster assignment\n",
        "five_cluster_center = five_cluster.cluster_centers_"
      ],
      "execution_count": 32,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_4VCzoOSA1tx",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "######  Evaluate Model 1"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BskPsOWK3CsM",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "###### Assess the Model with [Silhouette Coefficient](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.metrics.silhouette_score.html).\n",
        "Silhouette coefficient \"reflects the strength of a classification to the nearest crisp cluster compared to the next best cluster\" (Everitt, et al. 2001, p. 168)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Wm_pccH83CAu",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 34
        },
        "outputId": "0a28956b-299b-470b-d75c-edfcaf0cc38e"
      },
      "source": [
        "metrics.silhouette_score(subset1, five_cluster_labels, metric = \"euclidean\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": 33,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "0.2783669937395087"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": []
          },
          "execution_count": 33
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YE70WRzA5UWi",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "###### Assess the Model with [Calinski-Harabasz Index](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.metrics.calinski_harabasz_score.html).\n",
        "\n",
        "The Calinski-Harabasz index evaluate the cluster validity based on the average between cluster sum of squares and within cluster sum of squares."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DjTpRvvK3A0S",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 34
        },
        "outputId": "c7c97120-8fb0-4700-ef12-38d6f2d20989"
      },
      "source": [
        "metrics.calinski_harabasz_score(subset1, five_cluster_labels)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 34,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "2901.2430097720535"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": []
          },
          "execution_count": 34
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_D1aq5_p7aSF",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "##### 3.1.2 Use Elbow Method to Detemine the Optimal k Value"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pgiS42kED2Ii",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "# Calculate the sum of squared error for the clusters\n",
        "\n",
        "sum_of_squared_error = []\n",
        "for i in range(1, 15):\n",
        "  opt_cluster = KMeans(n_clusters= i, max_iter=1000)\n",
        "  opt_cluster.fit(subset1)\n",
        "  sum_of_squared_error.append(opt_cluster.inertia_)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 35,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cXjyPOkEEunR",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 295
        },
        "outputId": "a34d55b7-4214-478e-f0b7-049e961f114d"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Plot the SSE result by cluster value (k)\n",
        "plt.plot(range(1, 15), sum_of_squared_error, 'bx-') \n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Value of K\") \n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Sum of Squared Error\") \n",
        "plt.title(\"Elbow Method to Determine Optimal k \")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "execution_count": 36,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "image/png": "\n",
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": []
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dpISmJUY2Bpm",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "#### 3.1.3 Subset1 with Optimal k Value\n",
        "Conduct k-means cluster with 3 cluster solution"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GO6l8DBtGIIK",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "optimal_cluster = KMeans(n_clusters=3, init = 'k-means++', n_init=30, max_iter=300, random_state= 30).fit(subset1)\n",
        "# Array for cluster assignment from the five cluster result\n",
        "optimal_cluster_labels = optimal_cluster.labels_\n",
        "# Centroids of the 3 clusters\n",
        "optimal_cluster_center = optimal_cluster.cluster_centers_"
      ],
      "execution_count": 37,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {

        "colab_type": "code",

          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 0
        },
        "outputId": "d9064d11-e75b-4604-c290-3c508569e956"
      },
      "source": [
        "metrics.silhouette_score(subset1, optimal_cluster_labels, metric='euclidean')"
      ],
      "execution_count": 38,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "0.3649742702551647"

          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": []
          },
          "execution_count": 38
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9KST2FHSHIJk",
        "colab_type": "code",

          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",

        },
        "outputId": "6cd1151c-d7ef-42c6-c25b-7b4eee20d00d"
